                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18030914-21-off128 t18030914-21-crimeloc132"></join>, and deal with Mr. Dean: On Monday, the 22d of August, I received a half quartern loaf from the prisoner, and paid him five shillings and threepence farthing, which I owed for bread; he had been with bread before, and I paid it on account of Mr. Dean.</p>
